'''Hans Julius Riddervold''' (20 May 1901 <U+2013> 1986) was a Norwegian media executive.

He was born in [[Oslo|Kristiania]] as a son of attorney Hans Riddervold (1869<U+2013>1928) and Sophie Magdalena Haneborg.<ref name=hvem>{{cite encyclopedia|year=1973|title=Riddervold, Hans Julius|encyclopedia=[[Hvem er hvem?]]|editor=Steenstrup, Bj<U+00F8>rn|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo|url=http://runeberg.org/hvemerhvem/1973/0459.html|page=459|language=Norwegian|accessdate=13 July 2011}}</ref> He was a paternal great-grandson of politician [[Hans Riddervold]],<ref name=snl2>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Riddervold <U+2013> slekt|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Riddervold/slekt|language=Norwegian|accessdate=13 July 2011}}</ref> and his father was a first cousin of [[Nils Riddervold Jensen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nsd.uib.no/polsys/index.cfm?urlname=storting&lan=&MenuItem=N1_1&ChildItem=&State=collapse&UttakNr=33&person=12434|title=Nils Riddervold-Jensen|publisher=Norwegian Social Science Data Services (NSD)|language=Norwegian|accessdate=13 July 2011}}</ref> In 1925 he married Cathrine Huitfeldt, a sister of [[Henrik J<U+00F8>rgen Schibsted Huitfeldt]].<ref name=hvem/> They had the son [[Hans Huitfeldt Riddervold]].<ref name=snl2/>

He took his [[examen artium]] in 1920, and also graduated from ''Kristiania Handelsgymnasium'' in 1922. He worked in the company Stormbull from 1924, and then started in the family-owned newspaper ''[[Aftenposten]]''. He advanced to office manager in 1930, then manager from 1939. He also served a few years as chief executive officer. He was a board member from 1935, and after retiring in 1970 he was the board's chairman from 1970 to 1976.<ref name=hvem/><ref name=obit>{{cite news|title=Direkt<U+00F8>r Hans J. Riddervold d<U+00F8>d|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|date=11 August 1986|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He was the secretary of the employers' organization ''Osloavisenes Forening'' from 1934 to 1946.<ref name=hvem/> When this organization merged in 1947 to form ''Norske Avisutgiveres Landsforbund'',<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Norske Avisers Landsforening|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Norske_Avisers_Landsforening|language=Norwegian|accessdate=13 July 2011}}</ref> Riddervold was a board member from 1949 to 1967, chairing the organization from 1954 to 1957. He was also deputy chairman of the [[Norwegian News Agency]] from 1967 and chairman from 1971 to 1972. Outside of the media, he was a board member of [[Hofsfos Tr<U+00E6>sliperi og Papirfabrik]] from 1939.<ref name=hvem/>

He died in 1986.<ref name=hvem/>

